Subdeacons.—-The candidate received from the hands of the bishop the paten and chalice‚ and from those of the archdeacon the basin and ewer‚ together with a napkin. Before the traditio of these objects the bishop delivered a short address to the candidate, of which the text, preserved in the Missale Francorum, is as follows 2—-

Vide cujus ministerium tibi traditur. Et ideo si usque nunc fuisti tardus ad ecclesiam, amodo debes esse assiduus3 si usque nunc somno- lentus, amodo vigil; si usque nunc ebriosus, amodo sobrius3 si usque nunc inhonestus, amodo castus?
